        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6196",
        "content": "The necessity of this was felt no doubt by those who attributed so much importance to Logic; showing thereby that they were in search of helps for the understanding, and had no confidence in the native and spontaneous process of the mind.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-6196_41030_000003_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/6196/41030/6196_41030_000003_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6196",
        "content": "But this remedy comes too late to do any good, when the mind is already, through the daily intercourse and conversation of life, occupied with unsound doctrines and beset on all sides by vain imaginations.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-6196_41030_000003_000006",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/6196/41030/6196_41030_000003_000006.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6196",
        "content": "And therefore that art of Logic, coming (as I said) too late to the rescue, and no way able to set matters right again, has had the effect of fixing errors rather than disclosing truth.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-6196_41030_000003_000009",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/6196/41030/6196_41030_000003_000009.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6196",
        "content": "Now (to pause while upon this example and look in it as in a glass) let us suppose that some vast obelisk were (for the decoration of a triumph or some such magnificence) to be removed from its place, and that men should set to work upon it with their naked hands; would not any sober spectator think them mad?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-6196_41030_000003_000010",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/6196/41030/6196_41030_000003_000010.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6196",
        "content": "And if they should then send for more people, thinking that in that way they might manage it, would he not think them all the madder?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
